dalserver

Class Range

  • java.lang.Object
    • dalserver.Range
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Range>

    public class Range
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Range>
    The Range class implements a single Range element, and is used to contruct range lists. Ranges may consist of a single value or two values, maybe open or closed, and range values may be numeric or string (but the two cannot be mixed).

    • Constructor Detail

      • Range

        public Range(RangeType type,
     java.lang.String value1,
     java.lang.String value2,
     boolean order,
     boolean isoDate)
      throws InvalidDateException
        Create a new Range instance. Input null for a parameter value if it is not used.
        Parameters:
        type - The type of range.
        value1 - For a ONEVAL, LOVAL, or HIVAL range, the single value, or for a CLOSED range, the first value.
        value2 - The second value for a CLOSED range.
        order - Swap the two values if value2 < value1.
        isoDate - The range contains ISO date strings.
        Throws:
        InvalidDateException
